result.formatted_address: 17 McGregor St, Wan Chai, Hong Kong
result.name: Haven Restaurant

reviews.text: This hidden gem has a genuine feel to it and the food does not disappoint. The spicy shrimp as an appetiser and the apple crumble dessert was a true delight. Friendly staff and music by The Beatles and ABBA helped the overall experience to reach 5 stars. Oh, did I mention the wine was delicious as well?! Thanks for having us!
Friendly staff... Reasonably good food

We like coming here because of the cosy home cooking feel, and the free corkage. Cooking is localised European, so going for the grilled meat is a safe option as the owner cares about freshness and quality of the meat. The Tomahawk and lamb rack are both of good quality.

Great food and wine in a nice cosy atmosphere. Not fine dining, but more like a hidden gem with a home-style atmosphere. I have been several times and will undoubtedly try and go again when next in Hong Kong.
